        .segment.type
          h2 A campaign site for Taiwanese watch manufacturer ATOP

          p I only knew two things about Taiwan. Before I discovered the joys of MacBooks, I used to put together my own Windows builds because I am a huge dweeb. A key component of any PC is its motherboard. This is like the central nervous system of a computer and therefore one of its most important parts. A trusted name in mid-level motherboards at the time was ASUS, a manufacturer from Taiwan. This is all I knew about Taiwan until I came across these watches. Secondly, the U.S. refuses to recognise China as an independent country. None of that is relevant.

          h3 Findings

          p This project went through three rounds and by comparing v1 with v3, I can chart my progression as a designer in that time (2013–2016) . Here are my realisations:

          ul
            li Use vectors when you can
            li Control all the things that you’re able to control.
            li Design and control on the web is really large and interesting subject
            li Get out of the way. Focus on the important.


